Phase 5: Ranking Engine + AI Analysis

## Part A: Weighted Scoring & Leaderboard

### Scoring Algorithm
Composite score = weighted sum of normalized metrics (0-100 scale each):
- Impact (40%): normalized(time_saved) + normalized(cost_reduction) + normalized(accuracy) + normalized(yearly_usd_saved)
- Scalability (25%): scalability_score * 10
- Effort Efficiency (20%): yearly_usd_saved / max(dev_time_hours, 1) — ROI per dev hour
- Innovation (15%): innovation_score * 10

### API Endpoints
- GET /rankings — returns all cases sorted by composite score
  - Query params: impact_w, scalability_w, effort_w, innovation_w (default 40,25,20,15)
- GET /rankings/{case_id}/compare?with={other_id} — side-by-side comparison

### Frontend: "Leaderboard" Tab
- Ranked table with position (#1, #2, ...), composite score, and breakdown
- 4 weight sliders (Impact, Scalability, Effort Efficiency, Innovation)
- Scores recalculate in real-time as sliders move
- Top 3 highlighted with gold/silver/bronze
- Side-by-side comparison: select 2 initiatives to compare metrics

## Part B: Real-Time AI Analysis (Amazon Bedrock)

### AI-Powered Insights
When user clicks "AI Analysis" on any initiative, call Amazon Bedrock to generate:
1. Strengths & Weaknesses — based on the initiative's metrics vs library averages
2. Improvement Suggestions — specific recommendations to increase impact
3. Similar Initiatives — identify patterns from other cases in the library
4. Risk Assessment — flag potential issues (low accuracy, high dev time, etc.)

### API Endpoint
- POST /rankings/{case_id}/ai-analysis
  - Sends case data + library summary to Bedrock Claude
  - Returns structured AI analysis (strengths, weaknesses, suggestions, risks)

### Frontend
- "AI Analysis" button on each row in the leaderboard
- Modal popup showing the AI-generated analysis with sections
- Loading spinner while Bedrock processes

### Technical Approach
- Use boto3 with Amazon Bedrock Runtime (invoke_model)
- Model: anthropic.claude-3-haiku (fast, cheap) or claude-3-sonnet
- Prompt includes: case details, library averages, top performers for context
- Response parsed as structured JSON
- Fallback: if Bedrock unavailable, show "AI analysis requires AWS credentials"

### Configuration
- AWS credentials via environment variables or ~/.aws/credentials
- Model ID configurable in constants.py
- Max tokens: 1024 for analysis
